section.para:
 Guards are a possibility to reduce the amount of nesting. Heavily nested code is much harder to read. Bad:

public void foo() {
    if (conditionA) {
        if (conditionB) {
            if (conditionC) {
                // do some work
            }
        } else {
            throw new MyException();
        }
    }
}
        Good:

public void foo() {
    if (!conditionA) {
        return;
    }

    if (!conditionB) {
        throw new MyException();
    }

    if (!conditionC) {
        return;
    }

    // do some work
}
